yingyinNormal.en: I do. I have a daughter. I have feelings.

yingyinNormal.en: Jews don't have hell. We have acid reflux.

yingyinNormal.en: We have profits. They have integrity. I'm buying it!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们有利润，他们有诚信，我要买下它！

yingyinNormal.en: Do you have any Chap Stick? Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们有护唇膏吗？有。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you have one in mind? I do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有什么合适的人选吗？有。

yingyinNormal.en: Raj, do you have any questions for Amy?
yingyinNormal.zh: 拉杰，你有没有问题问艾米？

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. You guys have a minute? Uh, yeah, sure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗨，你们有时间吗？当然有。

yingyinNormal.en: I have some bad news.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我有个坏消息。

yingyinNormal.en: How long has he have?
yingyinNormal.zh: 他有多长时间？

yingyinNormal.en: You have me. You're right. I do have you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有我啊。你是对的，我的确拥有你。

yingyinNormal.en: Does he have a butthole?

yingyinNormal.en: Does she have any family?

yingyinNormal.en: Have you anything to say?

yingyinNormal.en: I have to meet Nate. Kinda have something special planned.

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The question of GDP and its usefulness <highlight>has</highlight> annoyed policymakers for over half a century.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 半个多世纪以来，GDP及其有效性的问题一直困扰着政策制定者。

examination_example.sentence: The interviewers <highlight>had</highlight> rated applicants on a scale of one to five.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 面试官按照从1到5的等级划分申请人。

examination_example.sentence: As the cost to everyone else <highlight>has</highlight> become clearer, politicians have begun to clamp down.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 由于带给其他人的损失已变得日益明显，政客们已经开始采取强硬手段。

examination_example.sentence: But the result was a new social pattern which, although it resembled European society in many ways, <highlight>had</highlight> a character that was distinctly American.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但结果是形成了一种新的社会模式，尽管在很多方面与欧洲社会相似，但它具有明显的美国特色。

examination_example.sentence: The danger will come with Charles, who <highlight>has</highlight> both an expensive taste of lifestyle and a pretty hierarchical view of the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 查尔斯亲王则面临危机，他既拥有奢侈的生活品味，又有浓厚的等级观念。

examination_example.sentence: The European Union Framework funding programs have long <highlight>had</highlight> a category specifically targeted at social scientists.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一直以来，欧盟框架下的基金项目有一个专门针对社会科学家的类别。

examination_example.sentence: Like the majority of authors, he <highlight>had</highlight> to suffer many disappointments and rejections along the way, but these made him all the more determined to succeed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 和大多数作家一样，他一路上也不得不遭受许多失望和拒绝，但这些都让他更加坚定了成功的决心。

examination_example.sentence: But to win over these young workers, manufacturers <highlight>have</highlight> to clear another major hurdle: parents, telling them to avoid the factory.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但为了赢得这些年轻工人的支持，制造商必须扫清另一个主要障碍:父母，告诉他们不要去工厂。

examination_example.sentence: Nearly 40% of emigrants <highlight>had</highlight> more than a high-school education, compared with around 3.3% of all Indians over the age of 25.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 近40%的移民接受过高中以上的教育，而25岁以上的印度人接受过高中以上教育的比例约为3.3%。

examination_example.sentence: Museums stopped exhibiting some of Gilardi’s artworks to <highlight>have</highlight> their ingredients analyzed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 博物馆停出展示吉拉迪的一些艺术品，以分析其成分。

examination_example.sentence: Machines <highlight>have</highlight> largely taken over planting, watering and harvesting crops such as com and wheat.

examination_example.sentence: She <highlight>has</highlight> decided to study Chinese history.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她决定学习中国历史。

examination_example.sentence: In the fictional worlds of film and TV, artificial intelligence (Al) <highlight>has</highlight> been described as so advanced that it is indistinguishable from humans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在电影和电视的虚构世界中，人工智能（AI）被描述为如此先进，以至于与人类无异。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 她有勇气跟随自己的心，做他真正喜欢的事情。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 恐怕我们必须严格限制你的饮食。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是想到我再也不必去参加训练了，我很开心。

word_usage.usage:
have与和动词同形的名词连用，表示一个短暂的动作：
have a talk (a look, a wash, a swim, a try, a smoke, a dream, a walk, a ride...) 
谈话(看一下，洗刷，游泳，试一试，吸烟，做梦，散步，骑车……)

have与其他名词连用：
①表示一种活动：have a lesson上课 have a meeting开会 have a haircut)理发
②表示患病：have a cold感冒 have a sore throat嗓子痛
③表示发生情况：have a baby生孩子 have a good harvest丰收

have后接复合结构时，所表达的含义不同，应根据语境确定宾补的形式：
①have sb. do sth. (接不带to的不定式)让某人做某事：
I would like to have Tom repair the TV.
我想让Tom修电视。
②have sth. done遭遇(受)到某种不好的情况：
Tom had his left leg broken in the car accident.
车祸中汤姆折了左腿。
③have sb./sth. doing sth.让某人/某物不停地做某事(多用于否定句)：
The boss won't have you wasting time playing like that.
老板不会让你像那样浪费时间玩的。

examination_example.sentence: To <highlight>have</highlight> a meeting.

examination_example.sentence: I just <highlight>had</highlight> a dream.

examination_example.sentence: Our school plans to <highlight>have</highlight> some educational activities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们学校计划开展一些教育活动。

examination_example.sentence: When did we <highlight>have</highlight> the school leavers' party？

word_usage.usage: have表示一般意义上的所有关系时，不能用于被动结构。过去式和过去分词均为had。

have to表示“不得不”，变否定句和疑问句时要借助于 do 或 does。
如：We don’t have to rush, there’s plenty of time.
我们不必着急, 有的是时间。（朗文）

have sth done的含义是"让别人做某事”，并不是自己亲自去做，其中have为使役动词。
如：I had my hair cut.
我理过发了。

have可协助构成完成时态。具体包括：
现在完成时：have+过去分词，描述过去发生的动作对现在的影响或结果。
I’ve finished my work.
我完成我的工作了。（牛津）
过去完成时：had+过去分词，描述的动作发生在“过去的过去”。
By the lime I got to the bus station，the bus had left.
在我到达公共汽车站之前，公共汽车已经离开了。
have可根据语境翻译为很多意思，可灵活理解。如：have dinner 吃晚餐。have piano class 上钢琴课。
